\newlabel{figure-error-in-approximation}{{\relax 1.11}{24}{The thick black curve is the graph of a function $f$ and the thinner black line is its tangent line $f(a) + df_a$ are depicted in black. On a small input $h$, the ``error in approximation'' function $r$ outputs the vertical distance indicated in red}{figure.1.11}{}}
